Musquash is a synonym for muskrat, of Algonquin Indian origin, but my
dictionary claims their range is just US & Canada.  Not directly related to
the thread, history lovers should hunt out Carleton Gadjusek's (Nobelist)
book titled (I think) Viral Hemorrhagic Fevers and Mycotoxicoses of the
USSR, published around 1950.
